'''Canadian Australians''' refers to [[Australians]] who identify as being of [[Canadian]] descent. It may also refer to Canadian immigrants and expatriates residing in Australia. According to statistics from 2006, there were as many as 21,000 Australians who have Canadian ancestors.<ref>[http://www.ausstats.abs.gov.au/ausstats/free.nsf/Lookup/C41A78D7568811B9CA256E9D0077CA12/$File/20540_2001%20(corrigendum).pdf AUSTRALIANS' ANCESTRIES]</ref>

[[File:Australian Census 2011 demographic map - Inner Sydney by POA - BCP field 1408 Canada Total.svg|thumb|left|upright=1.5|People born in Canada as a percentage of the population in [[Sydney]] by postal area.]]

