{{Infobox person | name = Marilyn Jean Hartman | image = <!-- filename only, no "File:" or "Image:" prefix, and no enclosing [[brackets]] --> | alt = <!-- descriptive text for use by speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software --> | caption = | birth_name = <!-- only use if different from name --> | birth_date = <!-- {{birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} for living people supply only the year with {{Birth year and age|YYYY}} unless the exact date is already widely published, as per [[WP:DOB]]. For people who have died, use {{Birth date|YYYY|MM|DD}}. --> | birth_place = | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (DEATH date then BIRTH date) --> | death_place = | nationality = American | other_names = | occupation = | years_active = | known_for = Stowing away on commercial airline flights | notable_works = }}
'''Marilyn Hartman''' (b. 1951&ndash;52<ref name="guardian">{{cite news|last1=Eskanazi|first1=Joe|title='Serial stowaway': how does a 66-year-old woman keep sneaking on to flights?|url=https://www.theguardian.com/society/2018/jan/24/serial-stowaway-marilyn-hartman-mental-health-homeless|accessdate=29 January 2018|publisher=The Guardian|date=2018-01-25}}</ref>), known as the "Serial Stowaway," is an [[United States|American]] woman known for [[stowaway|stowing away]] on more than 20 commercial airline flights since 2014.<ref name="npr">{{cite news|last1=Shapiro|first1=Ari|title=The Case Of The Serial Stowaway, Marilyn Hartman|url=https://www.npr.org/2018/01/26/581142460/the-case-of-the-serial-stowaway-marilyn-hartman|accessdate=29 January 2018|work=NPR.org|language=en}}</ref>
==Incidents== *On August 4, 2014, Hartman boarded a flight from [[Mineta San Jose International Airport]] to [[Los Angeles International Airport]] without a ticket. Flight attendants detected her upon landing in Los Angeles, and Hartman was arrested and charged with trespassing.<ref name="nbcbayarea">{{cite news|last1=Kovaleski|first1=Tony|title=Stowaway Arrested at LAX After Boarding Flight from SJC|url=https://www.nbcbayarea.com/news/local/Marilyn-Hartman-LAX-Stowaway-Arrested-Southwest-Flight-from-San-Jose-270076971.html|accessdate=29 January 2018|work=NBC Bay Area|language=en}}</ref> *On February 9, 2015, Hartman flew from Minnesota to Florida without a ticket. She was arrested after checking into a hotel under another person's name when that person arrived at the hotel. She was charged with fraud by impersonation and other crimes.<ref name="nbcnews">{{cite news|last1=Johnson|first1=M. Alex|title='Serial Stowaway' Marilyn Hartman Arrested Again, This Time in Florida - NBC News|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/serial-stowaway-marilyn-hartman-arrested-again-time-florida-n303291|accessdate=29 January 2018|work=NBC News|language=en}}</ref> *On January 14, 2018, Hartman snuck onto a plane from [[Chicago O'Hare International Airport]] to [[London Heathrow International Airport]], after failing the previous day to board a flight to [[Connecticut]]. Not having a passport, she was sent back to the United States by British immigration officials, where she was arrested and charged with theft.<ref name="chicagotribune">{{cite news|last1=Ford|first1=William Lee, Liam|title='Serial stowaway' got past TSA, spent night at O'Hare before flight to London: Prosecutors|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/news/local/breaking/ct-met-serial-stowaway-london-flight-court-20180120-story.html|accessdate=29 January 2018|work=Chicago Tribune|date=January 20, 2018}}</ref>
